Several dependencies and similar territories with broad autonomy are also found within or in close proximity to Europe. This includes [[Åland]] (an [[counties of Finland|autonomous county]] of Finland), two [[Danish Realm|autonomous territories of the Kingdom of Denmark]] (other than Denmark proper), three [[Crown Dependencies]] and two [[British Overseas Territories]]. [[Svalbard]] is also included due to its unique status within Norway, although it is not autonomous. Not included are the three [[countries of the United Kingdom]] with devolved powers and the two [[Autonomous Regions of Portugal]], which despite having a unique degree of autonomy, are not largely self-governing in matters other than international affairs. Areas with little more than a unique tax status, such as the [[Canary Islands]] and [[Heligoland]], are also not included for this reason.

